OL,3,CFamilies to take legal action against
OL,4,Ccouncil over paedophile headteacher
OL,6,FFamilies who say their children were
OL,7,Fsubjected to abuse by convicted
OL,8,Fpaedophile Neil Foden are planning to
OL,9,Ftake legal action against Gwynedd
OL,10,FCouncil.
OL,12,FFoden, 66, was convicted at Mold Crown
OL,13,FCourt of 19 offences, including 12 of
OL,14,Fsexual activity with a child,
OL,15,Finvolving the abuse of four girls
OL,16,Fbetween 2019 and 2023.
OL,18,FHe was sentenced to 17 years in prison.
